-- Pegas Nonwovens Falls Most in Five Months After Reporting Loss
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-03-15T09:44:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-15/pegas-nonwovens-falls-most-in-five-months-after-reporting-loss.html
Pegas Nonwovens SA (PEGAS) , a Czech maker
of textiles used in hygiene and healthcare, dropped the most in
almost five months after publishing a fourth-quarter loss today.  The stock fell as much as 2.9 percent, its biggest intraday
decline since Oct. 24, and traded down 2.3 percent at 438 koruna
by 10:16 a.m. in Prague. The  PX (PX)  equity gauge was little changed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  